unittitle_ssm: Kevin Kennedy Ephemera and Photographs Collection
abstract_ssm: Kevin Kennedy (1937-2016) was a native of County Galway in Ireland and worked as a photographer in New York City, contributing to publications like The Irish Echo. Kennedy was affiliated with Irish civic organizations like the United Irish Counties Association and the New York County chapter of the Ancient Order of Hibernians. He was also devoted to fundraising on behalf of the Irish Guide Dogs for the Blind. This collection consists of photographs, photo negatives, newspapers, magazines, newspaper clippings, social event programs, religious booklets, church related materials, artifacts, correspondence, and a scrapbook.
corpname_ssm: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives
